  "prompt": "What is the English word for the Tagalog word \u201ckinikilig\u201d?",
  "response": "The English word that is often used to translate the Tagalog word \"kinikilig\" is \"giddy\" or \"thrilled.\" It describes a feeling of exhilaration, sometimes romantic excitement, that makes someone feel fluttery or elated. The context of how \"kinikilig\" is used can slightly change the ideal translation, but \"giddy\" is usually a close match.",
